PL/SQL -TRIGGER


1.      Create a trigger to handle updates to the customer table.



mysql> delimiter //
mysql> create trigger cust_trig after update on Customer for each row begin insert into cust set cid = old.id,cname = old.name,addr = old.address,
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.01 sec)

mysql> create table cust(cid int primary key,cname varchar(10),addr varchar(20),loc varchar(10),phno int );
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.03 sec)


mysql> select * from Customer;
